title: RHG1111_hg19_accepted_hits
extract_protocol_ch1: Single cells were processed for RNA-seq using Nextera XT kits (Illumina). Cell lysis, reverse transcription (SMARTer Ultra Low RNA kit, Clontech) and PCR amplification (Advantage® 2 kit, Clontech) were performed on the C1™ Auto-prep module.
extract_protocol_ch1.1: Approximately 0.15 ng of cDNA from each cell was processed for RNA-seq using Nextera XT DNA library preparation kits (Illumina).
data_processing: Illumina HiSeq 4000 reads were trimmed and clipped for quality control in Trimmomatic.
data_processing.1: Read quality was checked for each sample using FastQC.
data_processing.2: High-quality reads were then imported into TopHat v2.0.8 for alignment into BAM files.
data_processing.3: BAM files were imported into the RNA-Seq pipeline of Partek Genomics Suite, version 6.6, and RPKM counts were calculated (RefSeq release 2016-8-1). Inclusion included a minimum RPKM value of 50.0 in at least 25% of cells. RPKM values were quantile normalized.
data_processing.5: Supplementary_files_format_and_content: 293alphaandbetacells.txt: Tab-delimited text file includes normalized RPKM values for each sample.

extract_protocol_ch1.1: Approximately 0.15 ng of cDNA from each cell was processed for RNA-seq using Nextera XT DNA library preparation kits (Illumina).
description.3: The paired-end raw data files are loaded at SRA as single-end files.
data_processing: Illumina HiSeq 4000 reads were trimmed and clipped for quality control in Trimmomatic.
data_processing.1: Read quality was checked for each sample using FastQC.
data_processing.2: High-quality reads were then imported into TopHat v2.0.8 for alignment into BAM files.
data_processing.3: BAM files were imported into the RNA-Seq pipeline of Partek Genomics Suite, version 6.6, and RPKM counts were calculated (RefSeq release 2016-8-1). Inclusion included a minimum RPKM value of 50.0 in at least 25% of cells. RPKM values were quantile normalized.
data_processing.5: Supplementary_files_format_and_content: 293alphaandbetacells.txt: Tab-delimited text file includes normalized RPKM values for each sample.
